.TH SIMPLE_SHELL 1 "April 2026" "simple_shell 0.4" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
simple_shell \- simple UNIX command line interpreter

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B simple_shell

.SH DESCRIPTION
.B simple_shell
is a minimalist UNIX command line interpreter written in C.
It mimics basic behavior of
.BR sh (1)
by reading user input, parsing commands, searching for executables using the
.B PATH
environment variable, and executing programs using system calls.

The shell displays a prompt, waits for user input, executes commands, and
repeats this cycle until the user exits.

It does not support advanced shell features such as pipes, redirections,
quoting, or scripting.

.SH FEATURES
- Displays a prompt and waits for user input
- Executes commands with arguments
- Resolves executables using PATH
- Handles end-of-file (Ctrl + D)
- Prints error messages when command is not found
- Supports built-in commands: exit, env

.SH BUILT-IN COMMANDS
.TP
.B exit
Exit the shell and terminate the program.

.TP
.B env
Print the current environment variables.

.SH USAGE
Interactive mode:
.PP
.RS
$ ./simple_shell
.br
($) ls
.br
($) env
.br
($) exit
.RE

Non-interactive mode:
.PP
.RS
echo "/bin/ls" | ./simple_shell
.br
cat file.txt | ./simple_shell
.RE

.SH EXECUTION FLOW
User input
.br
→ getline()
.br
→ parse command
.br
→ PATH lookup
.br
→ fork() (if command exists)
.br
→ execve() in child process
.br
→ wait() in parent process
.br
→ display prompt again

.SH RETURN VALUE
0 on success, non-zero on error.

.SH ERRORS
If a command is not found, an error is printed in the format:
.PP
.RS
./simple_shell: 1: command not found
.RE

The program name corresponds to argv[0].

.SH REQUIREMENTS
- Ubuntu 20.04 LTS
- gcc -Wall -Werror -Wextra -pedantic -std=gnu89
- Betty coding style
- No memory leaks
- Max 5 functions per file

.SH SEE ALSO
sh(1), bash(1), execve(2), fork(2), wait(2), getenv(3)

.SH AUTHOR
This project was written for educational purposes to understand UNIX
process creation, system calls, and shell behavior.
